 GUSTY WIND CONDITIONS PREVAILED WHEN THE AIRPLANE WAS ON FINAL 
APPROACH AND IT ENCOUNTERED A WIND SHEAR.  THE PILOT SAID HE APPLIED 
FULL POWER AND ROTATED THE NOSE UP; HOWEVER, HE WAS UNABLE TO ARREST 
THE DESCENT IN TIME TO PREVENT THE AIRPLANE FROM TOUCHING DOWN IN A 
GRASSY AREA 10 FEET SHORT OF THE RUNWAY.  THE AIRPLANE THEN BOUNCED 
INTO THE AIR AND CAME TO REST ON THE RUNWAY WITH COLLAPSED LANDING 
GEAR. 
 AN ENCOUNTER WITH WINDSHEAR WHICH RESULTED IN THE AIRPLANE LANDING 
HARD AND SHORT OF THE RUNWAY.  A FACTOR RELATED TO THE ACCIDENT WAS 
THE GUSTY WIND CONDITIONS. 
